# Terraform Built-in Functions and File Handling

A small hands-on practice project to understand some commonly used Terraform built-in functions like:

* `upper()`
* `startswith()`
* `pow()`
* `merge()`
* `file()`

Along with working with:

* `locals`
* `outputs`
* external YAML files

---

# Terraform Configuration

```hcl
locals {
  Name = "National Highway"
  age  = 50
}

output "Road_name" {
  value = upper(local.Name)
}

locals {
  state = "state Highway"
}

output "Road_name_start" {
  # value = startswith(upper(local.state),"ROAD") #false
  # value = startswith(lower(local.state),"roa") #false
  # value = startswith(lower(local.state),"hig") #false

  value = startswith(lower(local.state),"sta") #true
}

output "arith" {
  value = local.age * 2
}

output "power" {
  value = pow(local.age, 2)
}

# Reads the content of a file and returns it as string
output "Below-is-the-details-of-user-file" {
  value = file("${path.module}/users.yaml")
}

output "merge" {
  value = merge(
    {
      Name = local.Name
      Age  = local.age
    },
    {
      forest = "Savana"
    }
  )
}
```

