# Understanding the Functions

## 1. upper()

Converts all characters into uppercase.

### Example

```hcl
upper(local.Name)
```

### Output

```text
NATIONAL HIGHWAY
```

---

## 2. startswith()

Checks whether a string starts with a specific character sequence.

### Example

```hcl
startswith(lower(local.state), "sta")
```

### Output

```text
true
```

---

## 3. Arithmetic Operation

Terraform can also perform mathematical calculations.

### Example

```hcl
local.age * 2
```

### Output

```text
100
```

---

## 4. pow()

Used for power calculations.

### Example

```hcl
pow(local.age, 2)
```

### Output

```text
2500
```

---

## 5. file()

Reads content from an external file.

### Example

```hcl
file("${path.module}/users.yaml")
```

This is useful when:

* reading shell scripts
* loading configuration files
* working with Kubernetes YAML manifests
* user data scripts

---

## 6. merge()

Combines multiple maps into a single map.

### Example

```hcl
merge(
  {
    Name = local.Name
    Age  = local.age
  },
  {
    forest = "Savana"
  }
)
```

### Output

```hcl
{
  "Age"    = 50
  "Name"   = "National Highway"
  "forest" = "Savana"
}
```

